<identifier>:
First character is a letter, any proceeding characters are letters or numbers. Maximum length of 30 characters.

<type>:
Primitive types : String, int, boolean

<value>:
An identifier or a literal

Method Declaration:
'method <identifier - name> params ([<type> <identifier - name>,...]) [returns <type>]'

Method Invocation:
'<identifier - methodName> ([<value> , ...])'

Variable Declaration:
'<type> <identifier - name> [= <value>]'

Print Statement:
'print <value>'

Return Statement:
'return <value>'

Operator:
+, - ,* , /, 

Expression:
‘<identifier> <operator> <value>’

Condition:
‘<identifier> <conditional-operator> <value>’

Conditional-operator:
‘>, <, >=, <=, ==’


Loop Structure:
‘loop ( <type> <identifier-name>=<value> ; <condition> ; <identifier-name> = <expression>){
<statements>     // Terminated by new line
 }’

Conditional
 ‘if(<condition>[ && <condition> |  || <condition>[]){
[else]
}’

Comments:
Anything followed by // 

Statement:
Anything terminating in \n

Array:
 ‘<type> ar <identifier> = [<value>[,<value>...]]’
